Pension Transitional Arrangement Directorate (PTAD) has said it will pay the first batch of the verified ex-workers and next of kin of the Nigerian Aviation Handling Company (NAHCO). PTAD said the action is in line with the takeover approval of pension- related matters of some agencies, privatized/liquidated by the Bureau of Public Enterprises in 2017, among which is the NAHCO. Its executive secretary, Dr Chioma Ejikeme explained that the Directorate carried out a physical verification and biometric capture exercise for eligible ex-workers and next-of-kin of deceased ex-workers of NAHCO during its nationwide Parastatals Pensioners Verification Exercise conducted in 2019. Subsequently, the collated data were subjected to rigorous due processes culminating in the computation and auditing of the entitlements of the verified ex-workers and next of kin, she said. She said the Directorate is prepared to make payment to the first batch of NAHCO ex-workers and NOKs that are eligible to receive the final payment. Dr. Ejikeme emphasized that for the pensioners and NoKs to access the benefit, it is pertinent to highlight certain salient points that define their eligibility: 